description: Penthouse living in a landmark Collins Street address
Positioned in the iconic 'Temple Court' building (c.1924), this double-storey penthouse offers sophisticated city living with sweeping views over Collins Street and the Yarra River.

Set high on the twelfth floor, the generous layout features a well-equipped kitchen with stainless steel appliances, marble splashback and LED lighting, adjoining an open-plan living and dining zone that flow seamlessly to a private outdoor terrace. There are two double bedrooms with built-in robes, including a king-sized main with a stunning ensuite.

Additional features include secure entry via Collins Street, one car space, split system heating and cooling, European laundry, guest powder room, linen curtains, and access to well-maintained common areas.

A rare offering in one of Melbourne's most distinguished heritage buildings, you're just footsteps from world-class dining, shopping, and entertainment, with trams, Flinders Street Station, and Southern Cross Station all within easy reach. Also close to Crown, Queen Victoria Market, and the city's famed laneways.
